article.headline: James Madison 69, Delaware 64
article.story: NEWARK, Del. (AP) -- Terrance Carter scored 28 points to lead James Madison to a 69-64 win against Delaware on Saturday. Joe Posey came off the bench to score 13 points for the Dukes (7-16, 4-9 Colonial Athletic Association). Calvin Cannon scored 21 points for the Blue Hens (4-20, 2-11 CAA), and Herb Courtney added 20 points. Two minutes after halftime, the Dukes were up by 18 after controlling the first half. But the Hens fought back with a 20-10 rally. The Hens pulled within one point, making the score 65-64 with 12 seconds to go. The Dukes scored on two free throws. Cannon, the CAA's leading free-throw shooter, was fouled and stepped to the line with seven seconds remaining, but he missed both shots. Carter was then fouled, and he sealed the win by making both shots.
